summary.purpose: Barrel file that aggregates and re-exports all type definitions from the types sub-module.
summary.problem_solved: Provides a single import point for all utility and socket types so consumers do not need to reference individual files within types/.

internal.why_used: Re-exports primitive utility types: NumberObject, TObject, Geo
Re-exports socket communication types: REDIS_UPDATES_PREFIX, SOCKET_EVENTS, SocketEventMap, RedisUpdateType, RedisUpdatePayload, SocketCallbackResponse, CollectionConfig

exports.name: global (re-export)
exports.description_one_line: Re-exports primitive utility types from types/global.ts

exports.name: socket (re-export)
exports.description_one_line: Re-exports socket and Redis communication types from types/socket.ts

symbols.name: global (re-export)
symbols.description_one_line: Barrel re-export of primitive utility types from types/global.ts

details.what_it_does: Makes NumberObject, TObject, and Geo available through the types barrel.

minimal_correct.title: Import Geo and TObject through the types barrel
minimal_correct.code:
import type { Geo, TObject } from 'akeyless-types-commons';
// Available because types/index.ts re-exports types/global.ts

symbols.name: socket (re-export)
symbols.description_one_line: Barrel re-export of socket and Redis communication types from types/socket.ts

details.what_it_does: Makes REDIS_UPDATES_PREFIX, SOCKET_EVENTS, SocketEventMap, RedisUpdateType, RedisUpdatePayload, SocketCallbackResponse, and CollectionConfig available through the types barrel.

minimal_correct.title: Import SOCKET_EVENTS through the types barrel
minimal_correct.code:
import { SOCKET_EVENTS } from 'akeyless-types-commons';
// Available because types/index.ts re-exports types/socket.ts
